104 (d) (1) Any person that advertises or facilitates the sale or resale of a
105 ticket to an entertainment event shall (A) disclose the total price of such
106 ticket, which total price shall include all service charges required to
107 purchase such ticket, and (B) disclose, in a clear and conspicuous
108 manner, to the purchaser of such ticket the portion of the total ticket
109 price, expressed as a dollar amount, that is attributable to service
110 charges charged to such purchaser for such ticket.
111 (2) Any person that advertises or facilitates the resale of a ticket to an
112 entertainment event via an Internet web site or online technology
113 platform, the primary purpose of which is to facilitate resales of such
114 tickets, shall disclose, in a clear and conspicuous manner, that the ticket
115 is a resale ticket that may be offered at a price that differs from the price
116 of a ticket to an entertainment event that is offered or sold by the
117 presenter of the entertainment event.
